One of the most important aspects of staying at the top is to concentrate your efforts on Search [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/profit-outlines/Profit_Outlines-Search_Engine_Optimization-_Importance_and_Beginnings_of_SEO.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Marketing on the Internet, regardless of what you are marketing, is an extremely competitive business.  If you don&#8217;t stay on top of your game, continually learning and implementing you&#8217;ll soon find yourself somewhat lost in the battle.</p>
<p>One of the most important aspects of staying at the top is to concentrate your efforts on Search Engine Optimization, SEO.  Search engines are perhaps the most profitable and most sought after marketing tools on the Internet today.  Sure, there are plenty of other ways to market your site or your product but many consider search engine traffic as the gold strike.</p>
<p><span id="more-12"></span></p>
<p>It is a well known and researched fact that the majority of web users who search the net only click on the links of the first page of a search.  By default, that is typically the first ten search results.  Getting your website in that first ten for your keywords or phrases increases the likelihood that someone is going to click through to your site and these visitors that come from the search engines bring us the most&#8230;MONEY!!</p>
<p>Optimizing your site to get into the upper results of the search engines involves the daily dedication to working with a variety of the tools and methods that are proven to build a site to its search engine potential.  This is a lot of work and includes many aspects but the results can be amazingly fruitful.</p>
<p>Your first steps in search engine optimization should be to completely familiarize with the keywords and phrases that your target market is likely to use when searching for your products or services.  If you&#8217;re marketing something that has extreme amounts of competition you should also be concentrating on the lesser searched keywords and phrases as well.</p>
<p>Try and look at this way, if you can rank well for ten lesser searched keywords, your traffic will be more and so will your profits than if you&#8217;re ranking poorly for one popularly searched keyword or phrase.</p>
<p>Once you figure out the keywords and phrases you want to optimize your pages for you should then begin building content and pages around those.  Every article, blog post or web page you put up should be concentrated on one keyword phrase or keyword and as you&#8217;re writing this content you will want to keep the words flowing naturally.</p>
<p>You don&#8217;t want to just randomly stick your word or phrase in, this comes off as unprofessionally written and will lower conversions.  In addition, search engines are growing smarter by the day and keyword stuffed pages are quickly finding themselves lost amongst the lower ranked pages.</p>
<p>As with everything involved with Internet Marketing, practice and test and practice and test.  In order to fully reap the great rewards from search engines that a well optimized page can garner, you need to keep a close on what&#8217;s working and what&#8217;s not.  Ditch what&#8217;s not, improve what is and repeat the cycle and you&#8217;ll soon find yourself climbing the SERPs and pulling in the cash.</p>
