      <description>When a person first gets started in affiliate marketing, or even when a person starts looking into becoming an affiliate marketer they quickly have dollar signs rolling their eyes into the back of their heads.  Everything looks rosy, every looks great and they think that in no time at all the money is going [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/profit-outlines/Profit_Outlines-Your_First_Affiliate_Marketing_Websites.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>When a person first gets started in affiliate marketing, or even when a person starts looking into becoming an affiliate marketer they quickly have dollar signs rolling their eyes into the back of their heads.  Everything looks rosy, every looks great and they think that in no time at all the money is going to show up at their door steps in golden wheel barrows.</p>
<p>The fact is that far less than 10% of affiliate marketers hit the mother lode overnight.  The fact is that when you research, visit with or take advantage of advice from successful affiliate marketers you will quickly find they made it to their pedestal through (old fashioned concept here): hard work.<br />
<span id="more-10"></span><br />
Your research has also shown you that one of the best ways to maximize your affiliate marketing efforts is to have your own affiliate website.  Putting together your first affiliate website, particularly if you are new to affiliate marketing, can at first seem a quite daunting task.  However, if you stick to the basics it is really quite simple and combined with your affiliate marketing efforts, rather helpful in filling your first wheel barrow.</p>
<p>First it is important to make a decision on what niche or product or service you are going to be promoting.  Many people, when first starting out, try to overload this by promoting as many different things as possible and end up slowing their affiliate marketing growth process by spreading their jam a little too thin.  Find one niche or product you&#8217;re comfortable with and start profiting with that one before adding another helping of spuds to your plate.</p>
<p>Now that you&#8217;ve decided the niche or product you&#8217;re going to start promoting as an affiliate and you&#8217;ve decided you want an affiliate website, it&#8217;s time to choose a domain name.  When you&#8217;re selecting a domain name for affiliate marketing purposes it is important to select one that contains pertinent keywords to what you&#8217;re going to be promoting.  This will help with better search engine listings and help return visitors remember your website.</p>
<p>Alright, so now you have your niche and your domain name.  You need a place to host your affiliate marketing website.  It is my opinion that hosting is the single most important aspect of your online business.  Without a reliable host, your Internet business will not succeed whether your an affiliate marketer or marketing your own products.  When you choose a web host, don&#8217;t simply take their word for their guarantees.  Spend some quality time reading reviews on web hosting and Internet marketing related forums.</p>
<p>Well, let&#8217;s get this sucker built.  If you have the funds available and have absolutely no knowledge of how to build a website you may want to consider outsourcing the work, however, it is always a good thing to know a little bit about what goes into this process.  So, if time permits it&#8217;s a good thing to build your first site yourself.  There are a ton of different resources on the Internet that easily guide you through this process.</p>
<p>When you&#8217;re building, or having built, any website you will want to make sure it contains solid and keyword rich content.  The content of your affiliate website serves dual purposes.  First, it sells whatever it is you have decided to sell and secondly, it&#8217;s the food search engines feed on.  Both are equally important as it doesn&#8217;t do you any good to get visitors if you can&#8217;t close the sale and it doesn&#8217;t do you any good to have killer selling techniques if you can&#8217;t bring in the visitors.</p>
<p>Your website should also be as simple as you can possibly make it without giving the impression of a half-assed job.  The goal is to have a quick loading website with easily accessible information that looks professional, clean and is clutter free.  Sure, it&#8217;s nice to fill your pages with all of the latest technology and the bells and the whistles but if it isn&#8217;t necessary to enhance your affiliate marketing techniques it&#8217;s just one more thing between your customer and the sales link or order button.</p>
<p>After you have built your first website for affiliate marketing purposes and start promoting it.  Stay attuned to your stats and to what is working and what isn&#8217;t.  Test, revise and test some more until you hit the combination that provides you the sales you expect you should be making.  Once you&#8217;ve successfully reached your goals with this affiliate website, then if you have the desire to move on and promote other products and services you&#8217;ll have your own road map to follow.</p>
<p>Matt</p>
