      <description>As with everything a plan will help you not only be more efficient but will also help you maximize your marketing efforts and help get more revenue out of your website it is important to first put into place a plan of action in regards to your websites design.

- If you&amp;#8217;re main purpose of building [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/profit-outlines/Profit_Outlines-Planning_Your_Website_For_More_Revenue.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>As with everything a plan will help you not only be more efficient but will also help you maximize your marketing efforts and help get more revenue out of your website it is important to first put into place a plan of action in regards to your websites design.<br />
<span id="more-9"></span><br />
- If you&#8217;re main purpose of building your website is for revenue purposes you should always keep asking yourself if a certain aspect will increase your revenue or will it harm the revenue potential of your website.  If you are unsure, test it.</p>
<p>- Evaluate which links will make you more money and which links will not.  When planning my website I like to make sure that as many as possible of my outgoing links are income generating links.  Ask yourself if it&#8217;s a link trade link, does the trade sufficiently benefit you by bringing in enough relevant traffic or back link to justify giving up that space on your page to a non-income generating link?</p>
<p>- Try and plan your website to keep the ads above the proverbial fold.  This is tricky because you want your website visitors to see both the worth of being at your site and your income generating links.  Plan your website so the very first item a person sees is an income generating link but try and be prudent about giving your visitor the information they came to without cluttering the space with ads.</p>
<p>These three quick tips are fairly quite obvious but sometimes often overlooked in the planning stages of a website.  Hopefully they help ya&#8217; out.</p>
<p>Matt</p>
